WEBVTT

00:17.475 --> 00:19.811
♪ Young man goes out ♪

00:19.894 --> 00:24.899
♪ Looking for the diamond in the sea ♪

00:28.653 --> 00:32.699
♪ Old man rows his boat to shore ♪

00:32.782 --> 00:36.077
♪ And falls on twisted knees ♪

00:38.663 --> 00:44.669
♪ And you'll drown
Before the water lets you in ♪

00:47.797 --> 00:54.721
♪ And you'll drown
Before the water lets you in ♪

02:20.849 --> 02:21.724
Fuck you.

02:21.808 --> 02:22.892
Fuck you!

02:31.609 --> 02:33.111
Fuck it, just drive.

02:34.487 --> 02:35.613
Hey, where are we going?

02:59.679 --> 03:00.638
Mom.

03:01.389 --> 03:02.640
Mom?

03:02.724 --> 03:03.975
Did you hear what I said?

03:05.476 --> 03:06.311
Mom?

03:11.524 --> 03:12.775
He didn't mean to do it.

03:18.489 --> 03:20.241
I think he did, Mom.

03:21.409 --> 03:23.161
I really think that he did.

03:23.244 --> 03:24.078
No.

03:25.121 --> 03:26.080
He was upset.

03:26.831 --> 03:27.832
He wasn't himself.

03:28.875 --> 03:30.960
He was furious at Danny.

03:34.923 --> 03:36.090
What does it matter now?

03:37.342 --> 03:39.177
What's done is done.

03:51.773 --> 03:52.774
No, Mom.

03:57.111 --> 03:58.738
That's what I'm trying to tell you.

04:00.031 --> 04:02.325
Is that Kevin's at Marco's right now,
trying...

04:04.118 --> 04:05.453
to get him to help us.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.960
But I don't know what's gonna happen.

04:13.670 --> 04:15.171
We have to protect your father.

04:17.757 --> 04:18.716
What?

04:19.467 --> 04:20.843
He didn't mean to do it.

04:29.727 --> 04:30.561
Mitzi?

04:33.523 --> 04:34.565
Mitzi.

04:35.692 --> 04:36.609
Mitzi, come on.

04:36.693 --> 04:37.902
Get in here right now.

04:41.572 --> 04:43.324
I'm not talking about Daddy, Mom.

04:48.121 --> 04:49.998
Please tell me you understand, Mom.

04:56.170 --> 04:58.172
Of course I do. I'm not senile.

05:01.050 --> 05:01.884
Tell me.

05:05.388 --> 05:06.806
I need to hear you say it.

05:25.366 --> 05:26.451
Damn dog.

05:26.534 --> 05:27.368
Mitzi.

05:33.249 --> 05:34.083
John.

05:37.170 --> 05:38.046
John killed him.

05:40.465 --> 05:41.799
Mitzi!

05:42.884 --> 05:43.968
And Kevin, you...

05:49.390 --> 05:50.767
Get in here!

06:01.527 --> 06:03.279
You all lied to me.

06:13.873 --> 06:14.832
Mitzi!

08:01.314 --> 08:03.774
Hey, I get carsick in the back, man.
How about if I drive?

08:03.858 --> 08:04.901
Keep fucking moving.

08:17.580 --> 08:19.081
I need you all in one place.

08:20.208 --> 08:21.834
We all have to be together.

08:22.376 --> 08:25.463
-Mom--
-Find Kevin, find John.

08:25.546 --> 08:28.382
-Tell them to come home right now.
-Kevin is talking to Marco.

08:28.466 --> 08:31.344
- John hasn't been answering his phone--
- Excuse me.

08:31.427 --> 08:33.971
Uh... I'm so sorry. Uh...

08:35.973 --> 08:38.059
Um... You know what? Never mind.

08:38.142 --> 08:40.228
-I'll figure it out.
-That's great, thank you.

08:40.311 --> 08:41.145
Okay.

08:42.939 --> 08:45.316
I mean, just real quick, and forgive me,

08:45.399 --> 08:48.819
but how do I know the difference
between a bad sunburn and sunstroke?

08:48.903 --> 08:50.488
Vomit. Thanks.

08:50.571 --> 08:52.823
-If you could just give us a minute?
-Oh, no, no.

08:52.907 --> 08:54.909
You go, Meg.
I'll take care of Mrs. Samuels.

08:54.992 --> 08:57.203
My husband's doing that. He's throwing up.

08:57.286 --> 08:59.539
-Oh, poor thing, you must be so worried.
-I am.

08:59.622 --> 09:01.874
-I'll come right over with you.
-Okay, thank you.

09:01.958 --> 09:02.792
Mom?

09:05.086 --> 09:07.838
We have a doctor I can call,
he'll be here in five minutes.

09:07.922 --> 09:10.925
Yeah, I kept telling Jonathan
all day on the boat to put on a shirt.

09:11.008 --> 09:13.219
Oh! Why don't they ever listen?

09:13.302 --> 09:14.762
What's wrong with them?

10:30.171 --> 10:32.256
Put the weapon on the ground!

10:32.340 --> 10:33.507
Hands behind your head.

10:36.093 --> 10:37.178
On the ground.

10:37.637 --> 10:38.512
Put it down.

10:39.639 --> 10:40.473
Now.

10:44.101 --> 10:45.269
Hands behind your head.

10:46.437 --> 10:48.439
-Listen--
-Hands behind your head.

10:52.860 --> 10:53.819
Detective Rayburn?

10:53.903 --> 10:54.779
Yes.

10:58.032 --> 11:00.493
Tammy Peters, FHP.

11:00.576 --> 11:01.410
Tammy.

11:04.830 --> 11:06.248
That is some crazy shit.

11:07.917 --> 11:08.751
You okay?

11:10.211 --> 11:11.045
Yeah.

11:12.588 --> 11:14.298
It's not something you see every day.

11:33.901 --> 11:34.735
Oh, fuck.

11:35.069 --> 11:37.321
Hey, Kevin, pick up your damn phone.

11:37.738 --> 11:39.615
Why, dude? Just leave me a message.

11:39.698 --> 11:41.784
--Kevin, it's Meg. Where are you?

11:41.867 --> 11:44.161
Call me back now. Stop fucking around.

11:46.372 --> 11:47.206
Fuck.

11:52.420 --> 11:55.297
You've reached
John Rayburn. Please leave a message.

11:55.881 --> 11:56.924
John, it's me.

11:57.007 --> 11:59.301
Please call me back, okay? Please try me.

11:59.385 --> 12:00.219
Thank you.

12:11.647 --> 12:13.983
I just saw your truck.
It's not looking too good.

12:14.942 --> 12:16.735
I'm happy to give you
a ride back to Largo.

12:19.238 --> 12:23.284
No, that's all right. I called a flatbed
and let my wife know what's going on.

12:23.367 --> 12:25.035
Everything's fine, I'm just waiting.

12:25.119 --> 12:28.205
All right,
I'll, uh, get a call in to animal control.

12:28.289 --> 12:30.249
Should be out in the morning for the body.

12:30.332 --> 12:31.834
Sure you're okay now, Detective?

12:33.377 --> 12:34.420
Yeah, thank you.

12:35.004 --> 12:35.838
Good night.

12:38.132 --> 12:38.966
Be safe.

13:18.839 --> 13:21.592
When I was growing up,
we didn't take a lot of car trips.

13:22.760 --> 13:27.181
But I think I remember the rules
to this game.

13:28.098 --> 13:31.477
Who here wants to play I Spy? Huh?

13:31.810 --> 13:34.688
I got you, don't worry, I'll start us off.
Don't sweat it.

13:35.439 --> 13:37.650
I spy...

13:39.026 --> 13:41.320
with my little eye...

13:42.738 --> 13:47.159
two motherfuckers who won't fucking
tell me what the fuck is going on!

13:47.451 --> 13:48.285
Fuck.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.467
Please, God, wake up.

14:45.551 --> 14:46.677
Wake, wake up.

14:48.888 --> 14:51.515
Should have fucking listened to me,
you fucking asshole.

14:53.642 --> 14:55.102
Such a fucking asshole.

14:57.187 --> 14:58.272
Oh, fuck.

15:31.889 --> 15:34.308
You've reached the voicemail
of Detective Marco Diaz.

15:34.391 --> 15:36.810
If this is an emergency,
please hang up and dial 911.

15:36.894 --> 15:38.938
Otherwise, leave a message
and have yourself a safe day.

16:15.849 --> 16:18.811
Do you know where
I could get a pizza this time of night?

16:19.895 --> 16:20.729
No, ma'am.

16:21.271 --> 16:22.690
Where you going, darling?

16:23.273 --> 16:24.525
I sure could use a ride.

16:26.902 --> 16:27.945
You dangerous?

16:30.239 --> 16:31.073
No.

16:31.782 --> 16:32.616
No, ma'am.

16:34.326 --> 16:35.953
You don't look dangerous.

16:38.706 --> 16:39.540
All right, then.

16:40.749 --> 16:43.669
AC is busted, seat don't go back,

16:44.169 --> 16:47.047
and I keep a .45 nearby at all times.

16:48.340 --> 16:49.508
Just so's you know.

16:55.973 --> 16:56.807
Your choice.

17:30.466 --> 17:31.467
Kevin.

17:36.430 --> 17:37.264
Kevin!

17:39.558 --> 17:40.851
Oh, shit.

17:56.366 --> 17:57.284
You got a story?

17:58.744 --> 18:00.204
I got nothing but time.

18:01.747 --> 18:03.582
♪ Found me somebody ♪

18:04.875 --> 18:06.710
♪ Better than you ♪

18:09.296 --> 18:11.590
Okay, you don't have to talk
if you don't want to.

18:12.925 --> 18:14.718
I'm just passing the hours.

18:14.802 --> 18:16.762
♪ Look at me now ♪

18:17.763 --> 18:18.764
Want a hit of this?

18:20.557 --> 18:22.309
♪ I'm doing okay ♪

18:22.976 --> 18:23.811
No.

18:24.436 --> 18:25.896
It's prescription.

18:27.231 --> 18:29.817
Whatever your trouble,
it'll ease your pain.

18:30.359 --> 18:33.028
♪ From the bottom to the top ♪

18:33.403 --> 18:37.783
♪ I hope those tears
Would never stop ♪

18:40.369 --> 18:42.663
♪ Night after night after night ♪

18:46.250 --> 18:49.294
♪ Until the heartache ♪

18:49.378 --> 18:51.755
♪ Didn't hurt me no more ♪

18:52.131 --> 18:53.841
♪ And I'm all over ♪

18:55.801 --> 18:57.511
Go slow, friend.

19:05.018 --> 19:06.603
It's been a long time.

19:17.197 --> 19:19.366
♪ It was a long way ♪

19:19.867 --> 19:23.787
The first time I ever smoked,
my brother Danny got me to roll a joint

19:23.871 --> 19:26.957
so we could get a couple of sisters
to go skinny dipping.

19:27.749 --> 19:30.169
Me and my sister never needed no joint.

19:31.962 --> 19:33.130
Still don't.

19:33.881 --> 19:35.966
What am I supposed to do?
He's not at Marco's.

19:36.049 --> 19:38.218
- He's not answering his phone.
- Hang on, Meg.

19:39.386 --> 19:42.431
Doctor Joe, thank you so much.

19:42.514 --> 19:44.057
Always happy to help, Sally.

19:45.058 --> 19:45.893
You're a doll.

19:46.852 --> 19:48.562
And John has my vote for sheriff.

19:48.937 --> 19:49.771
Fingers crossed.

19:51.481 --> 19:53.150
-Meg?
-Did you call Kevin?

19:53.650 --> 19:55.485
I, uh, I left a message.

19:55.569 --> 19:57.571
You don't think
he's drinking again, do you?

19:57.654 --> 19:59.239
I don't know. I don't know, Mom.

19:59.323 --> 20:00.616
Well, check his bars.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.034
Fuck.

20:06.955 --> 20:09.833
Hey, do you remember the first time
that your dad hit you, man?

20:09.917 --> 20:12.252
You remember that?
And you tasted your own blood...

20:14.087 --> 20:15.380
in the inside of your mouth?

20:17.049 --> 20:19.593
And you cut the inside of your lip
with your teeth?

20:20.719 --> 20:21.762
I don't wanna hurt you.

20:23.013 --> 20:24.932
I don't wanna have to hurt you so bad.

20:26.099 --> 20:27.559
I don't wanna have to hurt you.

20:28.393 --> 20:30.395
We still doing stone crabs
Saturday night?

20:30.479 --> 20:31.688
For sure.

20:31.772 --> 20:34.942
I know. I know, man.
I know this is how he does it, huh?

20:35.525 --> 20:38.779
This is how John Rayburn
cleans up his trash, man.

20:38.862 --> 20:41.615
Fuck. I'll tell you something, though.
John Rayburn ain't shit,

20:41.698 --> 20:43.659
'cause I'm used to motherfuckers trying
to kill me themselves.

20:43.742 --> 20:46.662
None of this middle-management,
punk-ass bullshit.

20:50.082 --> 20:51.792
I didn't feel that, bitch.

20:52.376 --> 20:54.086
You ain't shit.

20:57.297 --> 20:58.465
Fuckhead.

21:04.805 --> 21:05.722
Fuck.

21:07.391 --> 21:08.725
Yeah.

21:10.102 --> 21:11.561
Just sink into it.

21:12.729 --> 21:13.605
Let it all go.

21:16.024 --> 21:18.860
♪ No one here can love ♪

21:18.944 --> 21:20.696
I'm running. Running.

21:21.697 --> 21:25.284
I bet you a real angry son of a gun,
aren't you?

21:47.681 --> 21:48.515
I'm running.

21:49.057 --> 21:50.851
I heard you the first time.

21:51.560 --> 21:53.228
It's the only way to make it better.

21:53.312 --> 21:57.399
So, smash some shit, make a mess.

22:00.319 --> 22:01.611
I already did that.

22:02.738 --> 22:05.157
And the world didn't stop spinning.

22:08.660 --> 22:10.287
We are not the center...

22:11.371 --> 22:13.165
because there is no center.

22:18.795 --> 22:20.172
There is no center.

22:21.298 --> 22:22.966
I heard you the first time.

22:29.431 --> 22:31.141
Bus station's just up ahead.

22:33.101 --> 22:35.896
♪ Pack up all my cares and woes ♪

22:36.980 --> 22:38.690
♪ Here I go ♪

22:40.025 --> 22:41.943
♪ Singing low ♪

22:44.112 --> 22:46.740
-♪ Bye-bye... ♪
-♪ Bye ♪

22:46.823 --> 22:52.120
-♪ Bye, blackbird ♪
-♪ ...Blackbird ♪

22:52.788 --> 22:54.206
When's it gonna end, John?

22:55.082 --> 22:57.125
Hm? Heh-heh.

23:02.339 --> 23:03.340
When's it gonna end?

23:03.423 --> 23:09.596
♪ Bye-bye, blackbird ♪

23:12.099 --> 23:13.350
All right, almost there.

23:34.246 --> 23:35.080
Fuck.

23:35.163 --> 23:36.373
Let's go. Get it off.

23:42.170 --> 23:43.672
Fuck.

23:48.885 --> 23:49.803
There we go.

23:49.886 --> 23:51.555
Got a little trash
to take care of.

24:07.529 --> 24:09.364
Meg, where you been?

24:09.948 --> 24:12.826
Haven't seen you since I hit on you
at that full moon party.

24:12.909 --> 24:14.452
I've been busy with the campaign.

24:14.536 --> 24:16.288
Hey, have you seen my brother around?

24:16.371 --> 24:19.541
-Mm, the one with the preggers wife?
-Yeah, Kevin.

24:20.125 --> 24:21.793
Thought he was off the sauce.

24:21.877 --> 24:24.588
He is. I just was curious
if you'd seen him around.

24:24.671 --> 24:27.507
No, not for a month or more.
How about you, you want a taste?

24:27.591 --> 24:28.550
Oh, maybe later.

24:28.925 --> 24:30.427
Is that a promise or a tease?

24:32.846 --> 24:36.433
Hey. You haven't, for any reason,
seen either one of my brothers, have you?

24:42.272 --> 24:43.857
Jesus. Did you have a rough day?

24:44.524 --> 24:47.360
And night, and day before that,
and night before that.

24:49.112 --> 24:51.156
I just worked a triple. Thirty-six on.

24:53.533 --> 24:54.492
You okay?

24:56.036 --> 24:59.164
Was that a class in law school?
Dumb Questions?

25:01.208 --> 25:04.461
Sorry, I just found out this morning
my mom's really dying.

25:05.921 --> 25:06.963
Whoa, shit, sorry.

25:12.802 --> 25:13.637
You want a drink?

25:14.554 --> 25:15.805
Uh, no, I can't.

25:17.933 --> 25:20.602
Actually, you know what, fuck it.
I could have just a quick one.

25:23.939 --> 25:25.065
Hey, Lannie.

25:25.148 --> 25:26.233
Kevin.

25:26.316 --> 25:27.859
-Yes. Yes, sir.
-All I asked

25:27.943 --> 25:30.362
was for you to abide
by a few simple rules.

25:30.445 --> 25:32.822
-I know, and I fucked that up.
-What time is it?

25:32.906 --> 25:35.617
-I'm such a fucking idiot--
-Is it not past 10 p.m.?

25:36.284 --> 25:38.328
-It is definitely late.
-What does that mean?

25:38.411 --> 25:40.497
-I know, but--
-What do you know?

25:40.580 --> 25:43.333
I can't be here past 10 p.m.,
but you have to understand--

25:43.416 --> 25:44.501
True or false?

25:44.584 --> 25:46.753
You were just caught
sneaking around the docks,

25:46.836 --> 25:48.838
and you maybe saw some things.

25:48.922 --> 25:52.592
True, but you have to understand, sir,
I didn't have a choice.

25:52.676 --> 25:54.386
I didn't know where else to go.

25:59.683 --> 26:00.642
Why those?

26:01.101 --> 26:02.435
Yes.

26:02.519 --> 26:04.229
See? Look, this?

26:04.312 --> 26:06.356
This has nothing to do

26:06.439 --> 26:09.651
with me trying to have anything
to do with your guys,

26:09.734 --> 26:11.319
or whatever you got going here.

26:11.403 --> 26:13.780
Listen, let me tell you
what happened, okay?

26:13.863 --> 26:16.783
I go to see this guy that I know.

26:16.866 --> 26:20.745
This friend of mine--
Well, of my family's, really.

26:20.829 --> 26:23.290
And I went-- I went...

26:23.373 --> 26:26.126
I went to his house-- Oh, Jesus.

26:26.918 --> 26:27.919
I need your help, sir.

26:28.003 --> 26:30.088
-My help?
-I wanted to go talk to him

26:30.171 --> 26:33.174
about why he was treating
my family so badly, right?

26:33.466 --> 26:37.762
And it just kind of, like,
spun out of control, and-- And...

26:38.847 --> 26:42.350
He's-- He's just lying on the floor,
and I don't think he's breathing.

26:42.434 --> 26:43.685
Do not say another word.

26:43.768 --> 26:45.603
-Mr. Gilbert, I need--
-Stop talking.

26:46.062 --> 26:47.355
I have to ask you a favor.

26:47.897 --> 26:52.485
I need you to open your door
and step out of my vehicle.

26:52.902 --> 26:56.740
-Mr. Gilbert, please--
-And this conversation never happened.

27:08.126 --> 27:11.129
- Well, how much blow was he doing?

27:11.212 --> 27:13.381
-No, yeah.
-Yeah, right. Who the hell knows?

27:13.465 --> 27:16.259
He was just talking so fast
in the message.

27:16.343 --> 27:19.888
I remember that the first time
I ever did a bump was with him,

27:19.971 --> 27:22.057
and I was in tenth grade.

27:22.640 --> 27:23.600
Homecoming.

27:23.683 --> 27:25.435
Yes, that's right.

27:25.518 --> 27:28.480
Yeah, I remember
Danny was so pissed at Eric

27:28.563 --> 27:30.940
for getting his little sister,
the prom queen, high.

27:32.359 --> 27:33.610
I didn't know that.

27:33.693 --> 27:35.445
Yeah. Eric thought it was funny,

27:35.862 --> 27:38.365
and Danny didn't talk to him
for, like, a week or two.

27:41.242 --> 27:42.285
I didn't know that.

27:46.748 --> 27:48.124
When is the next bus?

27:48.792 --> 27:49.834
Check the board.

27:52.796 --> 27:54.464
There's nothing on the board.

27:54.547 --> 27:56.299
Then I guess you got your answer.

27:56.383 --> 27:58.593
You mean, there's not another bus?

27:58.676 --> 28:00.804
People lie. Board don't.

28:01.388 --> 28:04.099
You don't have anything going
to Jacksonville or somewhere up north?

28:04.516 --> 28:05.517
Sure, I do.

28:07.560 --> 28:09.979
-Well, I'll take a ticket.
-It'll be 4:50.

28:15.026 --> 28:18.113
The ticket's only $4.50?

28:18.697 --> 28:22.617
Sir, the next bus to Jacksonville
is 4:50 a.m.

28:24.035 --> 28:26.538
-There's nothing any sooner?
-Where you looking to go?

28:27.122 --> 28:28.957
I'm looking to go north or west.

28:29.499 --> 28:32.252
-Any city in mind?
-Yeah, any city that's north or west.

28:40.093 --> 28:42.721
I do got Atlanta at 4:00 a.m.,

28:42.804 --> 28:45.598
Charlotte at, uh, 15 past the hour,

28:46.141 --> 28:48.351
and Mobile by way of Tallahassee...

28:49.060 --> 28:50.979
half past the hour of cinco.

28:51.438 --> 28:53.606
Does any of that wet your whistle, hoss?

28:57.068 --> 29:00.780
...activity well below
the average of 12 named storms,

29:00.864 --> 29:04.993
six hurricanes and three major storms,
suggesting it might be over.

29:05.076 --> 29:08.663
This year a big difference.
The year also introduced...

29:08.747 --> 29:10.832
Okay, wait, wait. So, Eric called you?

29:11.499 --> 29:12.792
Yeah, but I couldn't answer.

29:13.585 --> 29:16.546
I was dealing with this 80-year-old woman,
ruptured spleen.

29:18.298 --> 29:20.091
He sounds really crazy on the message.

29:20.175 --> 29:23.344
It was like he's foaming at the mouth.
He's so mad.

29:24.220 --> 29:26.514
-And he sounds terrified.
-Why?

29:27.307 --> 29:28.767
I don't know.

29:28.850 --> 29:31.895
He needs money, he wants to leave town,
he wants me to call him.

29:32.687 --> 29:34.022
And so, did you call him?

29:34.564 --> 29:35.648
Of course.

29:36.691 --> 29:38.151
And?

29:38.860 --> 29:40.695
And now he's not answering.

29:41.404 --> 29:43.698
I told him I'm here,
so, you know, fuck it.

29:44.866 --> 29:48.703
Yeah, fuck it. These fucking brothers
not answering their fucking phones.

29:53.166 --> 29:55.126
That's my mom. I gotta pee anyway.

29:56.711 --> 29:58.880
-Wait, watch my purse, okay?
-Yeah.

29:59.631 --> 30:00.590
Hey.

30:01.049 --> 30:03.134
I can't find either of them anywhere.

30:03.218 --> 30:07.305
Go to the boatyard, and if he's not there,
